Disney argues that a parallel can be drawn between the Carano case and the =
Supreme Court=E2=80=99s decision in the 1980s to allow organizers of Boston=
=E2=80=99s St. Patrick=E2=80=99s Day parade to exclude gay pride marchers, =
and the 1987 decision by the 1st Circuit supporting the Boston Symphony Orc=
hestra=E2=80=99s right to disassociate itself from Vanessa Redgrave after t=
he actress made statements supporting the Palestine Liberation Organization=
=2E Distinguishing Carano=E2=80=99s situat=
ion, Garnett seemingly came to the=20=
conclusion that casting and the conveyance of an expressive message needn=
=E2=80=99t go hand-in-hand, while also turning away from recent cases over =
controversies like The Bachelor=E2=80=99s failure to feature Black men or t=
he Miss USA beauty pageant=E2=80=99s exclusion of transgender women. Disney=
 is adamant that Garnett=E2=80=99s opinion demands a reassessment.

There=E2=80=99s a good deal riding on Disney=E2=80=99s argument.
The Carano go-ahead ruling has already influenced another federal judge, wh=
o recently advanced a discrimination suit against CBS by a white, heterosex=
ual male scribe on SEAL Team who claims he was passed over for a staff writ=
er position. (Not incidentally, he=E2=80=99s being supported by the America=
 First Legal Foundation, the flagrantly litigious nonprofit founded by form=
er Trump advisor Stephen Miller.) And more cases are likely coming. With th=
e conservative legal community eager to assert a stronger influence in Holl=
ywood, and with Carano=E2=80=99s claim backed by Musk and spearheaded by ap=
pellate specialist Gene Schaerr, it=E2=80=99s clear the case was strategica=
lly designed for potential escalation to the Supreme Court. Whether that ha=
ppens now or later is unclear, but until then, Carano=E2=80=99s team will b=
e more than happy to interrogate Disney=E2=80=99s political values.

That=E2=80=99s it for today. I=E2=80=99ll see you on Thursday.

Matt

