ght: 30px; margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0;">Welcome back to What I=E2=80=
=99m Hearing+, Tuesday=E2=80=99s smarter and legally blonde stepsister to W=
hat I=E2=80=99m Hearing. Speaking of legal issues, I=E2=80=99m <i>very</i> =
curious how Warner Bros. Discovery will handle this lawsuit filed today by =
the widow of <b>Michael Crichton</b> over the upcoming Max medical series <=
i>The Pitt</i>, which began as a reboot of <i>ER</i>, the show that Crichto=
n famously created. <b>Sherri Crichton</b> claims the estate was cut out of=
 the reboot after she asked for a similar =E2=80=9Ccreated by=E2=80=9D cred=
it for her late husband. Producers then simply switched the setting from Ch=
icago to Pittsburgh, she alleges.  <br/><br/>Anyone can make a hospital sho=
w, of course, so I=E2=80=99m less interested in the fact that <i>The Pitt</=
i> shares with <i>ER</i> the same executive producers (including <b>John We=
lls</b>), star (<b>Noah Wyle</b>), writer, and studio. I=E2=80=99m
much more interested, as I think a court would be, in the creative expressi=
on itself: How much <i>The Pitt </i>as a show resembles what was going to b=
e the <i>ER</i> reboot, whether Wyle=E2=80=99s character and the scripts ar=
e substantially similar, what rights were promised in writing to the Cricht=
ons, and what the trail of internal correspondence says about efforts to mo=
rph the reboot into what is set to air on Max. I also do wonder if the old =
Warner Bros. would have just paid Sherri to get her on board. The Warners o=
f <b>David Zaslav</b>? Less likely.    <br/><br/>Anyway, today <b>Eriq Gard=
ner</b> has a packed docket, including a probing look at Live Nation=E2=80=
=99s efforts to prevent C.E.O. <b>Michael Rapino</b> from testifying in a c=
ase brought over the stampede deaths at a <b>Travis Scott</b> concert in 20=
21. It includes this doozy of an email Rapino wrote to colleagues in the im=
mediate aftermath: =E2=80=9CLet=E2=80=99s wait for confirmation on deaths. =
If 5 died we would cancel.=E2=80=9D Yikes.
Let=E2=80=99s dive in=E2=80=A6<br/><br/></p>
