=80=99s lawyers at Cravath. The entertainment giants have proposed to submi=
t their main brief by September 20, with FuboTV=E2=80=99s response due Nove=
mber 4, aiming for a hearing sometime in December and a ruling shortly ther=
eafter. That=E2=80=99s pretty optimistic: The 2nd Circuit usually takes <i>=
months</i> and sometimes even <i>years</i>
for a result.<br/><br/>While FuboTV isn=E2=80=99t opposing the rushed sched=
ule, it did take the opportunity on Monday to poke fun at Disney and Fox=E2=
=80=99s =E2=80=9Chyperventilation,=E2=80=9D noting the irony that both comp=
anies initially downplayed Venu as a =E2=80=9Cmarginal offering=E2=80=9D bu=
t are now framing the launch delay of their lower-priced, skinny bundle of =
